	   <tr><td colspan=2>Twinking, like most everything else, has its good and bad points.  As far as twinking alts, no I don't think there is anything wrong with it.  Do it if you want.  Don't if you don't.  Doesn't matter.<br><br>Twinking new players?  Not sure.  I gave some stuff to a friend new to EQ to help out.  It helps him stay alive a little more as he's learning the game.  He doesn't kill anything instantly, but has a small advantage.  True, his armor is better than most anything he could get for months but it still doesn't help THAT much (for example the YKs mentioned still wouldn't proc, and the new player could only weild one, anyway).<br><br>Power-levelling, on the other hand, just seems boring for all involved.  My main is a 51 druid, I get lots of "can I pay you to power level me?" tells.  Nope.  You just end up being bored then having a weak character because your skills lag, and because you have no idea what you are doing.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
